comment.narrative:
- Second Biennial Update Report published and submitted in accordance with the guidelines contained in Annex III of Dec.2/CP. 17
SBUR data revised and updated as of 2016 (as applicable) in the following areas:
- National circumstances and institutional arrangements relevant to the preparation of the national biennial update reports;
- National Inventory Report and nationally adopted emission factors up to 2014;
-The baseline and mitigation scenarios by 2035 for non-energy sectors validated to ensure alignment with relevant national priorities,  
- Co- benefits of the proposed actions in various mitigation scenarios analyzed
- Impact analyses of different policy instruments for GHG emission reduction carried out and recommendations provided;
- Monitoring and evaluation framework for the Action Plan of the FBUR .
- Technology, financial and capacity gaps and needs for implementation of mitigation actions identified, and recommendation for addressing the needs provided;
- Specific gender analyses carried out for energy and non-energy sectors and recommendations for gender mainstreaming provided; 
- Detailed analyses of the capacities (human and financial) to implement each of the steps of the domestic MRV system proposed in the FBUR carried out and recommendations to facilitate the establishment of the system provided;
- Capacity of relevant national Gender Focal Points strengthened to ensure that the Measurement, Reporting and Verification (MRV) of mitigation actions is gender-sensitive

- Second Biennial Update Report published and submitted in accordance with the guidelines contained in Annex III of Dec.2/CP. 17
SBUR data revised and updated as of 2016 (as applicable) in the following areas:
- National circumstances and institutional arrangements relevant to the preparation of the national biennial update reports;
